## Diagnostic Summary

Based on our analysis of the existing code and configuration, we've identified several potential reasons why the web app still isn't loading on GoDaddy hosting despite previous fixes:

1. **Content Security Policy (CSP) Restrictions**: The CSP in index.html and .htaccess may be blocking necessary Firebase connections.

2. **GoDaddy Hosting Limitations**: GoDaddy might have specific hosting restrictions that block certain Firebase connections.

3. **Script Loading Order**: There might be race conditions or timing issues with script loading.

4. **Firebase SDK Version Compatibility**: The app uses Firebase SDK 9.6.1, which might have compatibility issues with the configuration approach.

5. **Firebase App Check Issues**: The App Check initialization might be failing on GoDaddy.

6. **Missing Firebase Configuration Fields**: The configuration might be missing fields required by specific Firebase services.

7. **JavaScript Errors in Other Parts**: Errors elsewhere in the application might be preventing proper loading.

## Diagnostic Approach

We've created an advanced diagnostic tool (`firebase-advanced-diagnostics.html` and `firebase-diagnostics.js`) that will help identify the specific issue. This tool:

1. Tests connectivity to all required Firebase domains
2. Checks if the Content Security Policy is blocking any connections
3. Provides detailed logging of the Firebase initialization process
4. Captures and displays any JavaScript errors
5. Tests different Firebase configuration approaches

## Solution Strategies

Based on what the diagnostic tool finds, here are potential solutions:

### 1. If CSP Issues Are Detected

Update the Content Security Policy in both the HTML meta tag and .htaccess file to include all required Firebase domains:

```html
<!-- Updated CSP in index.html -->
<meta http-equiv="Content-Security-Policy" content="default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' https://www.googletagmanager.com https://www.google-analytics.com https://www.gstatic.com 'unsafe-inline'; style-src 'self' https://fonts.googleapis.com 'unsafe-inline'; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com; img-src 'self' data: https:; connect-src 'self' https://api.aisportsedge.com https://www.google-analytics.com https://firebaseinstallations.googleapis.com https://firebaseremoteconfig.googleapis.com https://firestore.googleapis.com https://firebase.googleapis.com https://identitytoolkit.googleapis.com https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com https://www.googleapis.com; frame-src 'self' https://accounts.google.com https://aisportsedge.firebaseapp.com; object-src 'none';">
```

```apache
# Updated CSP in .htaccess
<IfModule mod_headers.c>
  Header set Content-Security-Policy "default-src * data: blob: 'self' 'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval'; script-src * data: blob: 'self' 'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval'; style-src * 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src * data: blob:; font-src * data:; connect-src * https://firebaseinstallations.googleapis.com https://firebaseremoteconfig.googleapis.com https://firestore.googleapis.com https://firebase.googleapis.com https://identitytoolkit.googleapis.com https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com https://www.googleapis.com; frame-src *;"
</IfModule>
```

### 2. If GoDaddy Hosting Limitations Are Detected

#### Option A: Simplified Firebase Configuration

Create a more minimal Firebase configuration that only includes essential services:

